Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement on the passing of Nancy Reagan. They praised her for her grace, courage, and loyalty. They highlighted her accomplishments as an actress, First Lady of California, and First Lady of the United States. They also mentioned her dedication to public service, particularly in advocating for children's safety from drugs and providing comfort to cancer survivors, victims of gun violence, and Alzheimer's patients and their families. The Bidens expressed their condolences to the Reagan family.